{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01WMPFcqEeRktvs4YKvytc2y","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpackage v1\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n5\t)\n6\t\n7\t// +genclient\n8\t// +genclient:nonNamespaced\n9\t// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n10\t\n11\t// Proxy holds cluster-wide information on how to configure default proxies for the cluster. The canonical name is `cluster`\n12\t//\n13\t// Compatibility level 1: Stable within a major release for a minimum of 12 months or 3 minor releases (whichever is longer).\n14\t// +openshift:compatibility-gen:level=1\n15\t// +openshift:api-approved.openshift.io=https://github.com/openshift/api/pull/470\n16\t// +openshift:file-pattern=cvoRunLevel=0000_03,operatorName=config-operator,operatorOrdering=01\n17\t// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n18\t// +kubebuilder:resource:path=proxies,scope=Cluster\n19\t// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n20\t// +kubebuilder:metadata:annotations=release.openshift.io/bootstrap-required=true\n21\ttype Proxy struct {\n22\t\tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n23\t\n24\t\t// metadata is the standard object's metadata.\n25\t\t// More info: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md#metadata\n26\t\tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n27\t\n28\t\t// spec holds user-settable values for the proxy configuration\n29\t\t// +required\n30\t\tSpec ProxySpec `json:\"spec\"`\n31\t\t// status holds observed values from the cluster. They may not be overridden.\n32\t\t// +optional\n33\t\tStatus ProxyStatus `json:\"status\"`\n34\t}\n35\t\n36\t// ProxySpec contains cluster proxy creation configuration.\n37\ttype ProxySpec struct {\n38\t\t// httpProxy is the URL of the proxy for HTTP requests.  Empty means unset and will not result in an env var.\n39\t\t// +optional\n40\t\tHTTPProxy string `json:\"httpProxy,omitempty\"`\n41\t\n42\t\t// httpsProxy is the URL of the proxy for HTTPS requests.  Empty means unset and will not result in an env var.\n43\t\t// +optional\n44\t\tHTTPSProxy string `json:\"httpsProxy,omitempty\"`\n45\t\n46\t\t// noProxy is a comma-separated list of hostnames and/or CIDRs and/or IPs for which the proxy should not be used.\n47\t\t// Empty means unset and will not result in an env var.\n48\t\t// +optional\n49\t\tNoProxy string `json:\"noProxy,omitempty\"`\n50\t\n51\t\t// readinessEndpoints is a list of endpoints used to verify readiness of the proxy.\n52\t\t// +optional\n53\t\tReadinessEndpoints []string `json:\"readinessEndpoints,omitempty\"`\n54\t\n55\t\t// trustedCA is a reference to a ConfigMap containing a CA certificate bundle.\n56\t\t// The trustedCA field should only be consumed by a proxy validator. The\n57\t\t// validator is responsible for reading the certificate bundle from the required\n58\t\t// key \"ca-bundle.crt\", merging it with the system default trust bundle,\n59\t\t// and writing the merged trust bundle to a ConfigMap named \"trusted-ca-bundle\"\n60\t\t// in the \"openshift-config-managed\" namespace. Clients that expect to make\n61\t\t// proxy connections must use the trusted-ca-bundle for all HTTPS requests to\n62\t\t// the proxy, and may use the trusted-ca-bundle for non-proxy HTTPS requests as\n63\t\t// well.\n64\t\t//\n65\t\t// The namespace for the ConfigMap referenced by trustedCA is\n66\t\t// \"openshift-config\". Here is an example ConfigMap (in yaml):\n67\t\t//\n68\t\t// apiVersion: v1\n69\t\t// kind: ConfigMap\n70\t\t// metadata:\n71\t\t//  name: user-ca-bundle\n72\t\t//  namespace: openshift-config\n73\t\t//  data:\n74\t\t//    ca-bundle.crt: |\n75\t\t//      -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\n76\t\t//      Custom CA certificate bundle.\n77\t\t//      -----END CERTIFICATE-----\n78\t\t//\n79\t\t// +optional\n80\t\tTrustedCA ConfigMapNameReference `json:\"trustedCA,omitempty\"`\n81\t}\n82\t\n83\t// ProxyStatus shows current known state of the cluster proxy.\n84\ttype Prox